General Motors said Tuesday it will invest an additional $1 billion in US manufacturing operations and create 5,000 jobs in the coming years.The investments in new vehicle and advanced technology are tied to 1,500 new and &#8220;retained&#8221; jobs, while 450 will be returned to the US from Mexico, the company said in a statement. Those and other moves are expected to total 5,000 new US jobs over the next few years.-AFP